---
title: Deploy Pivotal Cloud Foundry&reg; (PCF) Elastic Runtime
---

From the offline Ops Manager, set the deployment and deploy PCF:

1. Set deployment:
<pre class="terminal">
$ bosh -n deployment /home/ubuntu/deployments/cf-manifest.yml
</pre>

1. Deploy:
<pre class="terminal">
$ bosh -n deploy
</pre>

1. Associate PCF Router with ELB:
  1. In the AWS Console, navigate to the EC2 dashboard and click on **Load Balancers**.
  1. Find the ELB named `pcf-pcf-elb` and click on the **Instances** tab.
  1. Click on the **Edit Instances** button and select the **PCF Router** instance to add to the ELB.
  1. Wait a moment for the health check to run and verify the instance status changes to `InService`.


1. Run bosh utilities to confirm successful installation:
<pre class="terminal">
$ bosh -n vms cf-899c17563cb354672cb0
$ bosh -n cck --report
</pre>

1. Run bosh errands to install Elastic Runtime features:
<pre class="terminal">
$ bosh -n run errand push-apps-manager
$ bosh -n run errand smoke-tests
$ bosh -n run errand notifications
$ bosh -n run errand autoscaling
$ bosh -n run errand autoscaling-register-broker
</pre>
1. Verify that you can log in to your **Apps Manager** using the admin credentials specified in the PCF manifest.